#MEM id=rio source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/rio/ADS-PRINCIPLES.md savings=6%
M|ADS-|> Lo|designing a paid cg, analyzing ad perf, writing an ad st brief, or diagnosing a conversion funnel problem.
M|ADS-|tx|---
M|Cont|Befo|
M|Cont|tx|1. Active vt (nz or hb)
M|Cont|tx|2. `roas_benchmark` from memory — what's the target we're optimizing toward?
M|Cont|tx|3. `active_campaigns_*` from memory — what's already running?
M|Cont|tx|4. `ad_budget_split` from memory — what's the approved channel allocation?
M|Cont|tx|5. fx's budget context — how much is available to spend?
M|Cont|tx|Never recommend a cg w/o a budget and a hypothesis. Spend w/o hypothesis is waste.
M|Cont|tx|---
M|Camp|All |
M|Camp|tx|```
M|Camp|Camp|awareness / traffic / conversion)
M|Camp|└── |cold / warm / retargeting)
M|Camp|└── |vd / carousel / static)
M|Camp|tx|└── cp (hl + body + CTA)
M|Camp|tx|```
M|Camp|tx|One cg = one objective. Never mix awareness and conversion in the same cg.
